14/06/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Mehmet Ali Talat, prime minister of the "Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus", said on Saturday (12 June) that Turkey should establish basic relations with the Greek Cypriot part of the island.
Referring to Cyprus's recently acquired EU membership, Talat said it would be in Turkey's interest to co-operate with all EU members.
His comments came during a meeting with EU Enlargement Commissioner Guenter Verheugen and European Court of Human Rights President Luzius Wildhaber.
(CAN, Anadolu Agency - 12/06/04)
